President Trump attended a roundtable discussion at Luke Air Force Base in Arizona. He thanked the military leaders and defense industry representatives for their work in producing the best military equipment in the world. He also discussed the importance of investing in a strong military and modernizing the nuclear arsenal. The President mentioned a recent $110 billion equipment order from a particular country and expressed his desire to maintain that order. He also touched on the topic of the Saudi journalist Jamal Khashoggi's murder, stating that the Saudi response was a good first step. He emphasized the importance of the U.S.-Saudi relationship and the economic benefits of the arms deal with Saudi Arabia. The President also discussed immigration issues and the need for stronger border security measures, including the construction of a border wall.